text:
Eugene S. "Gene" Fraise (May 7, 1932 – November 27, 2020) was an American politician. He was a member of the Iowa Senate from the 46th district from 1986 until 2013. He was born in West Point, Iowa. Fraise was a member of the Democratic Party.
Fraise died of COVID-19 on November 27, 2020, in West Burlington, Iowa at age 88.
